Here is how you can create such a JavaScript function:

```JavaScript
function extractCode(filename) {
    const regex = /([a-zA-Z0-9]{3})\.[a-zA-Z]{2,4}\.usfm$/;
    return filename.match(regex)[1];
}
```
The function `extractCode` takes as input a string representing the filename. 

This function uses a regular expression (regex) to find a match for a three character code followed by ".usfm". If a match is found, the matched substring (which represents the 3-character code) is returned; otherwise, null is returned.
